<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName LSID="46786109-F6CB-53C7-9075-0E4FF34E9B93" authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">Abia nitens (Linnaeus, 1758)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">Tenthredo nitens</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1758: 556. ♂ [because the conspicuous dark dorsal patches on abdomen are mentioned]. Syntypes (assumed). Type locality: Europe. Lectotype designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" author="Malaise, R" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B128" refString="Malaise, R, Benson, RB, 1934. The Linnean Types of Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Arkiv foer Zoologi 26(4 [A20]): 1-14. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" title="The Linnean Types of Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Arkiv foer Zoologi 26 (4 [A 20]): 1 - 14." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" year="1934">Malaise and Benson (1934)</bibRefCitation>
. LSUK. Images of the lectotype (LINN 2402) in dorsal and lateral view are available (
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" publicationUrl="http://linnean-online.org" refId="B175" refString="2022. . http://linnean-online.org" url="http://linnean-online.org" year="2022">The Linnean Society of London 2022</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo sericea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">Tenthredo sericea</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1767: 921. Sex not stated [but probably female, because dark dorsal patches on abdomen are not mentioned]. Syntypes (assumed). Type locality: Leipzig. syn. nov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia sericea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">Abia sericea</taxonomicName>
: 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" author="de Dalla Torre, CG" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B37" refString="de Dalla Torre, CG, 1894. Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[6] pp.+ pp. I-VIII +] 1-459. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" title="Catalogus Hymenopterorum hucusque descriptorum systematicus et synonymicus. Vol. 1: Tenthredinidae incl. Uroceridae (Phyllophaga &amp; Xylophaga). Guilelmus Engelmann, Lipsiae, [[ 6] pp. + pp. I-VIII +] 1 - 459." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.10348" year="1894">de Dalla Torre (1894)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Konow, FW" journalOrPublisher="Genera Insectorum" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 176" refId="B99" refString="Konow, FW, 1905b. Hymenoptera. Fam. Tenthredinidae. Genera Insectorum 29: 1 - 176" title="Hymenoptera. Fam. Tenthredinidae." volume="29" year="1905 b">Konow (1905b)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Enslin, E" journalOrPublisher="Izvestija Stavropol'skogo Entomologiceskogo Obscestva" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B44" refString="Enslin, E, 1917. Die Tenthredinoidea Mitteleuropas VI. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift (Beiheft 6): 539-662." title="Die Tenthredinoidea Mitteleuropas VI. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift (Beiheft 6): 539 - 662." year="1917">Enslin (1917)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Liston, AD" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B117" refString="Liston, AD, Spaeth, J, 2006. On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae). In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 129 - 138" title="On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae)." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">
Liston and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Späth">Spaeth</normalizedToken>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" author="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 1064" refId="B173" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2010. World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera). Zootaxa 2580 (1): 1 - 1064, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" title="World Catalog of Symphyta (Hymenoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2580.1.1" volume="2580" year="2010">Taeger et al. (2010)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.Costa" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia dorsalis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsalis">Abia dorsalis</taxonomicName>
Costa, 1859: 5-6. ♀. Holotype [not examined]. Type locality: Italy, Cape Miseno near Naples. syn. nov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abia nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was successively mentioned as occurring in Sweden by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fallen, CF" journalOrPublisher="Kongliga Vetenskaps Academiens nya Handlingar" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="179 - 209" refId="B48" refString="Fallen, CF, 1807. Foersok till uppstaellning och beskrifning a de i Sverige fundne Arter af Insect-Slaegtet Tenthredo Linn. Kongliga Vetenskaps Academiens nya Handlingar 28 (3): 179 - 209" title="Foersok till uppstaellning och beskrifning a de i Sverige fundne Arter af Insect-Slaegtet Tenthredo Linn." volume="28" year="1807">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Fallén">Fallen</normalizedToken>
(1807)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.67771" author="Dahlbom, G" journalOrPublisher="Berling, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B35" refString="Dahlbom, G, 1836. Prodomus Hymenopterologiae Scandinavicae. C. F. Berling, Lund, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.67771" title="Prodomus Hymenopterologiae Scandinavicae. C. F." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.67771" year="1836">Dahlbom (1836)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, CG" journalOrPublisher="Olsson, Lund" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 342" refId="B178" refString="Thomson, CG, 1871. Hymenoptera Scandinaviae (Tenthredo et Sirex Lin.). H. Olsson, Lund 1: 1 - 342" title="Hymenoptera Scandinaviae (Tenthredo et Sirex Lin.). H." volume="1" year="1871">Thomson (1871)</bibRefCitation>
, who all placed 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo sericea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Tenthredo sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its synonym. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Thomson’s">Thomson's</normalizedToken>
description of leg color indicates that he had before him specimens of the species called by 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" editor="Taeger, A" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="193 - 205" refId="B171" refString="Taeger, A, 1998. Bestimmungsschluessel der Keulhornblattwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera: Cimbicidae). In: Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Eds., Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 193 - 205" title="Bestimmungsschluessel der Keulhornblattwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera: Cimbicidae)." volumeTitle="Pflanzenwespen Deutschlands (Hymenoptera, Symphyta)." year="1998">Taeger (1998)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. sericea" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or perhaps 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. candens" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="candens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. candens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[not distinguished from the former in 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Thomson’s">Thomson's</normalizedToken>
time]. Influenced by the continued, widespread use of the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia nitens" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abia nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Scandinavian literature, 
<bibRefCitation author="Taeger, A" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="399 - 504" refId="B172" refString="Taeger, A, Blank, SM, Liston, AD, 2006. European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries. In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 399 - 504" title="European Sawflies (Hymenoptera: Symphyta) - A Species Checklist for the Countries." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">Taeger et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Andre, E" journalOrPublisher="Kommentierte Bestandsaufnahme. Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B4" refString="ArtDatabanken (2015) Roedlistade arter i Sverige 2015. [Introduction pp 1-17; Hymenoptera pp 92-97]. ArtDatabanken SLU, Uppsala, 1-209." year="1881">ArtDatabanken (2015)</bibRefCitation>
included Sweden within the range of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brevicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[as 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. nitens" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct.]. In fact, no Swedish specimens of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brevicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been located in the MZLU or NHRS collections, and there are no published records from other Fennoscandian countries. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Liston &amp; Mutanen &amp; Heidemaa &amp; Blank &amp; Kiljunen &amp; Taeger &amp; Viitasaari &amp; Vikberg &amp; Wutke &amp; Prous" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia brevicornis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abia brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to extremely dry, summer-warm sites, where its larval hosts occur (
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Scabiosa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scabiosa" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Scabiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp.) (
<bibRefCitation author="Liston, AD" editor="Blank, SM" journalOrPublisher="Goecke and Evers, Keltern" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" pagination="129 - 138" refId="B117" refString="Liston, AD, Spaeth, J, 2006. On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae). In: Blank, SM, Schmidt, S, Taeger, A, Eds., Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects. Goecke and Evers, Keltern: 129 - 138" title="On the Biology of Abia nitens (Linne, 1758): a Thermophile Sawfly with a Diurnal Larval Feeding-Pattern (Hymenoptera: Symphyta: Cimbicidae)." volumeTitle="Recent Sawfly Research: Synthesis and Prospects." year="2006">
Liston and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Späth">Spaeth</normalizedToken>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). Probably it has a strongly continental distribution: its most north-westerly known localities in Europe are in Central Germany, whereas it is not definitely known in France (
<bibRefCitation author="Noblecourt, T" journalOrPublisher="Office National des Forets, Laboratoire National d'Entomologie Forestiere, Quillan" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B137" refString="Noblecourt, T, 2020. Liste systematique des Hymenopteres Symphytes de France (2020-2). Office National des Forets, Laboratoire National d'Entomologie Forestiere, Quillan" title="Liste systematique des Hymenopteres Symphytes de France (2020 - 2)." year="2020">Noblecourt 2020</bibRefCitation>
), and a single old record from Spain needs confirmation. Although a presence of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. brevicornis" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="brevicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. brevicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in southern Sweden cannot be ruled out, we consider it likely that all references to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. nitens" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
auct. in Sweden relate to either 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. nitens" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" class="Insecta" family="Cimbicidae" genus="Abia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Abia sericea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sericea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">Abia sericea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] or 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. candens" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" rank="species" species="candens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="151">A. candens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
